{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"20d0bc12-4aba-4461-b61e-1ecc0d7825ba","content":"No files found in the workspace — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the CLR namespace and `x:DataType` on the root element:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme name\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"2\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`. Every `{Binding}` inside that scope is now compiled.\n\n## 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\n**Compiled bindings already emit build errors.** If you typo a property name (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a compiler error like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\nTo ensure this is fully active:\n\n| Setting | Where | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `x:DataType=\"...\"` | XAML root or any child element | Enables compiled bindings in that scope |\n| `<MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>` | `.csproj` `<PropertyGroup>` | **Fails the build** on any binding without `x:DataType` (catches forgotten pages) |\n\nAdd to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n## 3. Opting out locally\n\nIf a specific binding must stay interpreted (e.g., dynamically-typed context), use `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element to disable compiled bindings for that subtree only.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** Add `x:DataType` pointing to your ViewModel → bindings compile → typos and type mismatches become build errors. Enable `MauiStrictXamlCompilation` project-wide to guarantee no page is accidentally left untyped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a2c7338-0e4f-40e7-a7af-6cb81b5e8da3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking me to help them convert a hypothetical page. Since there are no files, I'll provide them with the guidance and example code directly.","outputTokens":736,"requestId":"7FD9:39A45D:61314E2:69F542C:69F155FC"},"id":"a65c0595-12b2-4ce2-a0a2-b00e71586434","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:24.222Z","parentId":"613886f9-c76c-4f6c-8c2c-bb497b5c082e"}
